T1  - Fair Pay for Fair Play: Estimating Pay Equity in Professional Baseball with Data Envelopment Analysis
AU  - Howard, Larry W.
AU  - Miller, Janis L.
Y1  - 1993/08/01
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256763
DO  - 10.5465/256763
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 882
EP  - 894
VL  - 36
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Data envelopment analysis shows promise for generating objective estimates of pay equity. Applied to performance and salary data for 433 professional baseball players, data envelopment analysis identified objectively underpaid, equitably paid, and overpaid players. The output also identified relevant referents for each player and quantified the relative influences of referents and all variables.
AB  - Data envelopment analysis shows promise for generating objective estimates of pay equity. Applied to performance and salary data for 433 professional baseball players, data envelopment analysis identified objectively underpaid, equitably paid, and overpaid players. The output also identified relevant referents for each player and quantified the relative influences of referents and all variables.
